[[牛津大学赛艇俱乐部|牛津大学赛艇俱乐部]]主席兼尾桨手马修·史密斯表示：“太让人高兴了，感觉还要一会儿才能完全适应”<ref name="bros">{{Cite news | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/other_sports/boat_race_2003/2923053.stm | title = Mixed emotions for brothers | publisher = BBC Sport | date = 2003-04-06 | access-date = 2021-03-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200628210504/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/other_sports/boat_race_2003/2923053.stm | archive-date = 2020-06-28 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。他感谢队友竭力抗争和对手的尊重，最终扭转史上最大的体重劣势<ref name="closest" /><ref name="titanic">{{Cite news | title = Oxford win by one foot after titanic struggle | first = Christopher |last=Dodd |page = 28 | date = 2003-04-07 | newspaper = The Independent}}</ref>。纳瑟科特自称“满以为输定了。有那么会儿我简直到了这辈子最低迷的时刻，突然之间就变成欣喜若狂”<ref>{{Cite web | title = Four brothers, two boats, one great race | first = Nicole | last = Martin | newspaper = The Daily Telegraph | date = 2003-04-07 | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1426833/Four-brothers-two-boats-one-great-race.html | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160229064646/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1426833/Four-brothers-two-boats-one-great-race.html | archive-date = 2016-02-29 | dead-url = no | access-date = 2021-03-23 }}</ref>。剑桥队划手詹姆斯·利文斯顿对以这么小的差距败北深表惋惜，希望当时能让时间停止，避免输掉这史诗般的比赛。剑桥队教练威廉姆斯自称此役失利实在“扎心”。<ref name="bros" />伍格表示失望，但比赛非常精彩，值得向牛津队脱帽致敬<ref name="epic" />。兰科夫事后表示这是他担任裁判期间最艰难的决定<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.britishrowing.org/upload/files/BoatRace/BoatRaceSupp09.pdf | format = pdf | publisher = British Rowing | title = Total Concentration | first = Maggie | last = Phillips | work = Rowing and Regatta | date = 2009-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180612162723/https://www.britishrowing.org/upload/files/BoatRace/BoatRaceSupp09.pdf | archive-date = 2018-06-12 | access-date = 2018-06-12 | dead-url = no | page = 6 }}</ref>。

五获奥运会金牌的[[史蒂夫·雷德格雷夫|史蒂夫·雷德格雷夫]]向胜方俱乐部主席马修·史密斯颁奖<ref name="Livingston" />，宣称这一定是世世代代所见最精彩的比赛，值得大家牢记在心<ref name="grauniad">{{Cite web | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20161202015917/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2003/apr/07/highereducation.students | url = https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2003/apr/07/highereducation.students | title = Oxford overcome weight of history – by 12 inches | first = Paul | last = Weaver | newspaper = The Guardian | date = 2003-04-07 | dead-url = no | access-date = 2021-03-23 | archive-date = 2016-12-02 }}</ref>。估计全球有四亿人通过电视收看赛事转播<ref name="grauniad"/>，其中英国就有五百余万人在[[英國廣播公司第一台|英國廣播公司第一台]]了解实况<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.broadcastnow.co.uk/close-finish-puts-smile-on-the-old-boat-race/1116319.article | work = Broadcast | title = Close finish puts smile on the old boat race | date = 2003-04-30 | access-date = 2021-03-23 | archive-date = 2020-09-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200923042054/https://www.broadcastnow.co.uk/close-finish-puts-smile-on-the-old-boat-race/1116319.article }}{{subscription required}}</ref>。詹姆斯与戴维·利文斯顿兄弟合著《血浓于水》（{{lang|en|''Blood Over Water''}}）重现比赛过程<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.britishrowing.org/2010/04/blood-over-water/ | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200930161102/https://www.britishrowing.org/2010/04/blood-over-water/ | publisher = British Rowing | title = Blood Over Water | date = 2010-04-01 | access-date = 2021-03-23 | archive-date = 2020-09-30 }}</ref>。

马丁·克罗斯（{{lang|en|Martin Cross}}）在《[[衛報|衛報]]》发文，称比赛结果激动人心且重燃公众兴趣<ref name="die" />；《[[獨立報|獨立報]]》刊登作家兼新闻工作者克里斯托弗·多德（{{lang|en|Christopher Dodd}}）的文章，称赞比赛“非常精彩，是意志长久抗争的杰出体现”<ref name="titanic" />，他在《赛艇新闻》（{{lang|en|''Rowing News''}}）也表达类似看法<ref name="rowingnews" />。《[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]》的雷切尔·夸瑞尔（{{lang|en|Rachel Quarrell}}）宣告牛津此胜堪称“史诗”，“不会再有更精彩的牛津剑桥赛艇对抗赛”<ref name="epic" />。[[西蒙·巴恩斯|西蒙·巴恩斯]]（{{lang|en|Simon Barnes}}）在《[[泰晤士报|泰晤士报]]》发表的文章写道：“接近终点，牛津队船桨激起的水泡刚领先那么一丁点儿，才过一秒又变成落后。如果剑桥队划出最后一桨时正好抵达终点，而不是像现实那样一桨划完、另一桨还没开始时抵达，结果就可能截然不同。”<ref name="flick" />

